It's always super interesting to carry out explanatory data analysis on issues that matter to me the most, especially in regards to home demolishments in Palestine."
""
"In my recent project, I performed EDA on a dataset on Forced Home Demolitions in Palestine from the years 2004-2021."
""
"I also used Logistic Regression, a supervised learning classification model (for categorical variables) that works best on small datasets. I trained the model to predict the area of demolishments."
""
"Link to project on my github: "

Support Vector Classification is used in Classification. It is used to fit the data you provide, returning a "best fit" hyperplane that divides, or categorizes, your data. "
""
"Catboost Classifier is an algorithm that works using decision trees. A decision tree is a flowchart-type object where feature values are used to identify which tree branch to pick until finally, a prediction is made."
""
"Random Forest Classifier is an algorithm that uses an ensemble of the decision trees trained on different random subsets of the data. "
""
"I used all three algorithms on a Cardio Fitness dataset where I try to predict what threadmill model a customer buys based on their information. Check it out on my Github! https://lnkd.in/gaCsKPnQ"
""
"#datascience  #github #algorithms #machinelearning #catboost #randomforest #supervisedlearning
